﻿FAQs    Answers
What is I-Venture@ISB?    I-Venture@ISB is an initiative aimed at fostering entrepreneurship and innovation through various programs and support mechanisms at Indian School of Business
What is the mission of I-Venture@ISB?    The mission of I-Venture@ISB is to support and nurture startups and entrepreneurial ventures by providing mentorship, funding, and a supportive ecosystem.
Who can benefit from I-Venture@ISB?    Students, entrepreneurs, innovators, and startups can benefit from I-Venture@ISB.
Where is I-Venture@ISB located?    I-Venture@ISB operates out of the Indian School of Business campuses in both Hyderabad (known as DLabs) and Mohali (known as AIC ISB).
How can I contact I-Venture@ISB?    You can contact I-Venture@ISB via their official website i-venture.org or email i-venture@isb.edu/contact@isbdlabs.org/contact@aicisb.org
What is the I-Sproute program?    The I-Sproute program is a flagship pre-incubation program designed to support idea-stage ventures.
How can I apply to the I-Sproute program?    You can apply to the I-Sproute program through the application portal on the I-Venture@ISB website.
What is the Technology Entrepreneurship Program (TEP) - Tricity Edition?    The Technology Entrepreneurship Program (TEP) - Tricity Edition is designed to ignite entrepreneurial flair among student innovators in the Tricity region.
What support does TEP provide to student innovators?    TEP provides mentorship and support in ideation, innovation, prototyping, and fundraising to student innovators.
What is the SISFS - AIC program?    The SISFS - AIC program provides financial support to selected startups through the Startup India Seed Fund Scheme.
How does SISFS - AIC support startups?    SISFS - AIC supports startups by investing in them and providing necessary resources for growth.
What is the SISFS - DLabs program?    The SISFS - DLabs program provides financial support to selected startups through the Startup India Seed Fund Scheme.
How does SISFS - DLabs support startups?    SISFS - DLabs supports startups by investing in them and providing necessary resources for growth.
What is the TRICOR Batch 4 program?    The TRICOR Batch 4 program is a flagship entrepreneurship program in collaboration with the Tribal Cooperative Finance Corporation Ltd (TRICOR) under the Telangana Government's Tribal Welfare Department.
How does TRICOR support tribal entrepreneurs?    TRICOR supports tribal entrepreneurs through capacity-building sessions and other resources.
What is Atal Catalysts @ ISB 2.0?    Atal Catalysts @ ISB 2.0 is a mentorship program in partnership with Atal Innovation Mission (AIM), NITI Aayog.
How does Atal Catalysts @ ISB support startups?    Atal Catalysts @ ISB supports startups through mentorship and guidance to take their digital products to market.
What is the Nidhi SSS (Seed Support Scheme)?    The Nidhi SSS (Seed Support Scheme) is a flagship business incubation program under the Department of Science and Technology (DST).
How does Nidhi SSS support startups?    Nidhi SSS supports startups by providing seed funding and incubation resources.
What is the Nidhi EIR (Entrepreneurs in Residence) program?    The Nidhi EIR (Entrepreneurs in Residence) program is an initiative by the National Science and Technology Entrepreneurship Development Board (NSTEDB) to support aspiring entrepreneurs.
How does Nidhi EIR provide support?    Nidhi EIR provides a monthly stipend to aspiring entrepreneurs to help them pursue their startup ideas.
What is the Agri & Food Accelerator program?    The Agri & Food Accelerator program supports startups in the agriculture and food sectors through mentorship and funding.
How does the Agri & Food Accelerator support startups?    The Agri & Food Accelerator helps startups in scaling their operations and accessing markets.
What is the I-WIN 2.0 program?    The I-WIN 2.0 program supports women-founded startups through mentorship, funding, and networking opportunities.
How does I-WIN 2.0 support women-founded startups?    I-WIN 2.0 provides tailored support to help women entrepreneurs grow their businesses.
What is the Cleantech Accelerator program?    The Cleantech Accelerator program supports startups in the clean technology sector.
How does the Cleantech Accelerator support startups?

How does Edurise 2.0 support Edtech startups?    Edurise 2.0 helps Edtech startups in scaling their solutions and accessing educational institutions.
What is the I-Heal @ ISB program?    The I-Heal @ ISB program supports healthcare startups through mentorship, funding, and resources.
How does I-Heal @ ISB support healthcare startups?    I-Heal @ ISB helps healthcare startups in scaling their innovations and accessing healthcare markets.
What is the Social Impact 2.0 program?    The Social Impact 2.0 program supports startups focused on creating social impact.

What are the eligibility criteria for I-Venture@ISB programs?    The eligibility criteria for I-Venture@ISB programs vary by program and are detailed on the program's application page.
What documents are required for application?    Required documents typically include a business plan, pitch deck, and founder information, but specifics vary by program.
